  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "O Lord, my soul convicted stands Of breaking all Thy ten commands: And on me justly might&#39;st Thou pour Thy wrath in one eternal show&#39;r.",
    "v2": "But thanks to God, its loud alarms Have warn&#39;d me of approaching harms; And now, O Lord, my wants I see, Lost and undone, I come to Thee.",
    "v3": "I know my fig leaf righteousness Can ne&#39;er Thy broken law redress; Yet in the gospel plan I see, There&#39;s hope of pardon e&#39;en for me.",
    "v4": "There, I behold with wonder, Lord! That Christ hath to Thy law restor&#39;d Those honors on th&#39;atoning day, Which guilty sinners took away.",
    "v5": "Amazing wisdom, pow&#39;r and love, Display&#39;d to rebels from above! Do Thou, O Lord, my faith increase To love and trust Thy plan of grace."
  },
